title: Maple-Glazed Ham
text: Using a sharp knife score the layer of fat on the ham in a criss cross fashion around meat with thin layer of fat.
Mix the glaze ingredients together and pour over the ham. Bake in oven preheated to 180Â°C for 30mins, making sure to baste well every ten minutes.
Allow to rest for 30 minutes or serve chilled.

title: Brownies
text: Preheat the oven to 180Â°C. Line a 23cmx33cm brownie pan with parchment paper, leaving roughly a 5cm overhang, to help remove the brownies later.

Sift the flour, cocoa powder and salt together into a bowl and set aside. In a medium pan set over medium heat melt the chocolate and butter together. Once fully melted whisk in the sugars, then remove from the heat. Firmly whisk in the eggs and vanilla until the eggs are combined and the batter has thickened slightly. Add the flour mixture and gently fold together. You want to fold it in completely, a few spots of flour is fine. Pour into the prepared pan and gently level out.
